100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 21, 1925, the world witnessed significant political shifts as the French government announced plans to increase military support for its territories in the Middle East amid rising tensions. In the United States, the ongoing Scopes "Monkey" Trial continued to draw national attention, pitting science against religious beliefs in a landmark debate over education. Additionally, the League of Nations convened to address growing concerns over global stability and economic recovery in the wake of the Great War.
